bij_summary_short: 3-5 alleged militants killed in strike on vehicle in Angor Ada/ Baghar, South Waziristan.
narrative: 4 drones hovered. 5 killed, 4 injured. 'No way to ascertain the identity of the slain people.'

bij_summary_short: 7-8 alleged militants killed in strike on van and possibly house in Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone attacked a pickup van in Datta Khel, killing 7 people.

bij_summary_short: 3-5 alleged militants killed in strike on car in Doga Mada Khel, North Waziristan.
narrative: Friday afternoon, drone hovering. 5 people, 4 missiles. Bodies unrecognizable 'due to burning.'

bij_summary_short: Attack on compound kills 4-10 alleged militants in Sandasa, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
narrative: 6 people killed when US drones hit a house in Mir Ali.

bij_summary_short: 3-6 alleged militants killed in strike on pick-up truck in Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
narrative: Minutes later, another drone fired two missiles at a vehicle nearby, killing 3 people.

bij_summary_short: 4-6 alleged militants killed in attack on moving vehicle in Tappi, North Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone killed 4 people in a vehicle near Miranshah.

bij_summary_short: 4-7 alleged militants killed in strike on van in Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
narrative: Missiles killed 7 people in a van. Official: 'I do not know whether there was a high-value target.'

bij_summary_short: US airstrike in the city of Zinjibar, most likely a drone, killed Abu Ali al-Harithi and a number of other militants as well as four civilians.
narrative: 7 people killed, including 4 civilians, when US missiles struck the coastal town of Zinjibar.

bij_summary_short: Up to 5 named al Qaeda killed among 8-12 alleged militants in strike on orchard in Ghwa Khwa, South Waziristan.
narrative: While drinking tea in an apple orchard, Ilyas Kashmiri and 9 other men were slain from above.

bij_summary_short: House destroyed killing 7-9 alleged militants in Shalam Ragzhai, South Waziristan.
narrative: At about 2am, three US drone missiles hit a house in Shalam Raghzai, killing 7 people.

bij_summary_short: 8-10 killed, including possibly 7 civilians, in attack on seminary in Wacha Dana, South Waziristan.
narrative: 8-10 people were killed in a second attack. Witnesses: '7 civilians' among the dead.

bij_summary_short: 3-5 alleged militants killed in attack on car in Darnashtra, South Waziristan.
narrative: Third strike of the day killed 3 people in a vehicle. Up to 5 drones seen flying in the area.

bij_summary_short: 18-23 alleged militants killed in attack on compound in Zoynari, South Waziristan.
narrative: In the forested valley of Shawal, 18-23 people were killed in a house.

bij_summary_short: 4 militants or civilians killed in strike on truck in Shawal, South Waziristan.
narrative: After following a pickup truck, four US drones killed 4 people, blowing the vehicle 'to pieces.'

bij_summary_short: At least one top insurgent was killed in the US military-led strikes by unmanned aircraft.
narrative: An unmanned aircraft killed 1 person in Zinjibar.

bij_summary_short: A security official from Abyan province claimed that one of three linked strikes against militants resulted in the deaths of three civilians.
narrative: Nader Shadadi was not home. His mother, and 11-year-old Moti’a Haidara, were killed by a US drone.

bij_summary_short: Attack on house kills 3-10 alleged militants in Wana, South Waziristan.
narrative: 10 people killed in a house near Wana.

bij_summary_short: None killed as car occupants escape drone strike in Karez, South Waziristan.
narrative: No one was killed. Drone missiles hit a car, but its occupants had escaped into an orchard.

bij_summary_short: 5-6 civilians killed in strike on car near Miranshah, North Waziristan.
narrative: 5 civilians -- a taxi driver, two students, a pharmacist, and a shopkeeper -- were killed in a car.

bij_summary_short: Six civilians were wounded in an apparent drone strike targeting 'senior jihadists'. However, no AQAP militants were reported to be hit in the attack.
narrative: At least 6 Yemeni civilians wounded by a US drone.

bij_summary_short: 7 alleged militants and rescuers killed in strike on car in Khardand, Kurram Agency.
narrative: 5 people killed in a car. As tribesmen rushed to the scene, drones struck again. 2 more killed.

bij_summary_short: 3-5 alleged militants killed in strike on house in Zarakai, Kurram Agency.
narrative: Minutes later, a suspected US drone attacked a nearby house, killing 5 people.

bij_summary_short: In the first known lethal drone strike in Somalia, Predators struck a militant training camp 10km south of Kismayo. Further missiles hit a second target near the airport. At least 2 people were killed.
narrative: In Somalia's first known lethal drone strike, 1-3 people were killed and 'others' were injured.

bij_summary_short: 6-12 killed in strike on truck and compound in Shawal, North Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone fired 2 missiles at a vehicle in Shawal, the first of two attacks on the day.

bij_summary_short: 14-21 alleged militants killed in attack on 'training camp' in Shakai, South Waziristan.
narrative: Hajji, a local resident, said 20 civilians were killed in a house. Officials: 12 'militants.'

bij_summary_short: Named Western al Qaeda militant among 4-6 reported killed in strike on guesthouse in Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
narrative: 4-6 people killed. The guesthouse, located close to a market, 'was completely destroyed.'

bij_summary_short: 5-12 killed, including possibly 5 civilians, in strike on van in Borvaika/ Gorwak in North Waziristan.
narrative: 10 people killed Monday. US drones attacked a house and car in the village of Gorwaik.

bij_summary_short: 12-25 alleged militants killed in strike on compound in Gorvak/ Shawal, North Waziristan.
narrative: On Tuesday morning, a US drone fired 2 missiles at a house in Gurwak, killing 12-25 people.

bij_summary_short: An attack on a house and/ or car killed 5-13 alleged militants, including 'foreigners'. Three students 'with militant links' were killed in either this or Ob230, named as Hafiz Bilal, Waheed Ullah and Fayaz. Barmal, South Wazir
narrative: Up to 13 people, including 3 students--Hafiz, Waheed, and Fayaz--were killed by a US drone.

bij_summary_short: 13-15 alleged militants killed in strike on car and house in Dre Nishatr, Shawal valley, North Waziristan.
narrative: Linked attacks on a house and car killed up to 15 people, including 4 civilian rescuers.

bij_summary_short: 8-9 people were killed in strike on car. At least one civilian casualty. Datta Khel, North Waziristan.
narrative: In the 4th attack of the day, missiles struck a car, killing 'a local villager.'

bij_summary_short: At least six people were reported killed in a US strike in Abyan province. The New York Times claimed the same strike killed eight, whilst CNN claimed that as many as 50 people were killed.
narrative: An airstrike, likely including a drone, killed up to 50 people. CNN reported 30 civilians dead.

bij_summary_short: A US strike on a car targeted Fahd al-Qusaa, also known as Quso, an al Qaeda leader and suspect in the USS Cole bombing. He reportedly left the car minutes earlier and was unharmed.
narrative: A US strike on a car targeted Fahd al-Qusaa, but he left moments before the missiles.

bij_summary_short: 4 alleged militants killed in Khushali Toori Khel, Mir Ali, North Waziristan.
narrative: Drone missiles destroyed a house in Mir Ali, killing 4. 'The death toll was expected to rise.'

bij_summary_short: Five AQAP militants, including a field commander, were killed by a US drone strike on Karadeef, in western Zinjibar.
narrative: At least 5 people killed in Karadeef.

bij_summary_short: Two or three airstrikes killed up to 16 alleged militants, including local al Qaeda leader Nader Shadadi.
narrative: 15 people killed and 17 wounded in three air strikes. Officials: US Predator drones responsible.

bij_summary_short: 4-6 people - possibly all civilians - killed in strike on car in Azam Warsak, South Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone killed 4-6 people in Azam Warsak. Riaz, a local resident, said all were civilians.

bij_summary_short: 3-4 alleged militants killed in strike on car. Qutab Khel, North Waziristan.
narrative: 3 people killed in a drone strike on a moving car. Bodies were damaged 'beyond recognition.'

bij_summary_short: 20-25 killed and vehicle destroyed in pre-dawn strike. Miranshah, North Waziristan
narrative: A US drone killed 21 people. Not known 'if any high-profile militants were among the dead.'

bij_summary_short: 4-7 killed, including possibly 3-4 civilians, and 2 injured in a strike on a housing compound and vehicle. Miranshah, North Waziristan.
narrative: As people started their Ramadan fast, missiles struck near a girls' school, killing 4 people.

bij_summary_short: 3-4 killed and 2 injured in strike on house. Shin Warsak, South Waziristan.
narrative: Up to 4 people killed in Shin Warsak, reportedly while 'at the house of a tribal elder.'

bij_summary_short: 4-7 killed, including possibly 0-4 civilians, and 3 injured in strike on vehicle. Norak, North Waziristan.
narrative: In the first of two attacks, a US drone hit a house, 'killing 3 men, 2 children and a lady.'

bij_summary_short: The News was the single source for reports of a second strike on a house on August 22 that killed a family of Arabs, 'three men, two children and a lady. Local villagers said an Arab family was residing in the house and all those died in the missile attack were Arab nationals.' The newspaper speculated that this strike killed Atiyah abd al-Rahman (see Ob239).
narrative: An hour after locals ended their daily fast,' an unmanned Predator drone killed 4 people.

bij_summary_short: 6 killed in Abyan. Source unable to confirm whether air strike was Yemeni Air Force or US drone
narrative: 6 killed in Abyan. Source unable to confirm whether air strike was Yemeni Air Force or US drone.

bij_summary_short: Urdu TV station Ajj reports that an evening strike killed up to seven alleged militants in an unspecified location in North Waziristan, a day after the end of the four-day Eid holiday. No further details are known from this single source.
narrative: One day after Eid, a US drone killed 7 people in North Waziristan.

bij_summary_short: 10 al-Qaida militants were killed and dozens of others were injured' when a US drone struck 'several targets' in Abyan, Xinhua said. Predator drones also 'bombed an abandoned hotel and a primary school on the eastern outskirts of Jaar city' in Abyan.
narrative: 10 people died when a US drone struck an abandoned hotel and primary school in Abyan.

bij_summary_short: 4-5 killed and 2 injured in strike on 10th anniversary of 9-11. Hisokhel, North Waziristan.
narrative: A CIA drone destroyed a car, killing 4-5 people.

bij_summary_short: There were two alleged US drone strikes reported on this day, killing 4 and up to 7, respectively.
narrative: In the first of 2 airstrikes, US drones killed 4 people. Their target, Saeed al-Shehri, escaped.

bij_summary_short: A second strike reportedly targeted militants in the southern port city of Shaqra, killing up to seven people.
narrative: In the second air strike of the day, 7 people were killed.

bij_summary_short: 3-8 alleged militants killed and 3-4 injured in strike on house and vehicle. Khushali, North Waziristan.
narrative: Two US drone missiles hit a house in the village of Khushali Turikhel, killing 6 people.

bij_summary_short: The United States launched a series of drone attacks on al-Shabaab in Kismayo, according to residents, who reported attacks on three locations.
narrative: US drones attacked the port city of Kismayo. Residents reported 'explosions around the city.'

bij_summary_short: Up to four killed and up to two injured in strike on a compound. Azam Warsak, South Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone fired 2 missiles at a vehicle in Azam Warsak, narrowly missing the people inside.

bij_summary_short: 3-4 killed and 5 injured in strike on a vehicle. Baghar, South Waziristan.
narrative: A suspected US drone killed 3 people in a car.

bij_summary_short: Anwar al-Awlaki, the US-born cleric, became the first US citizen to be deliberately killed by the CIA in a drone strike. 3 others were killed as well.
names: [Anwar al Awlaki, Samir Khan, Abu Muhsen al Maribi, Salem al Marwani]
narrative: Two US citizens--Anwar al-Awlaki and Samir Khan--were killed by US drones.

bij_summary_short: Four Somali farmers were reported to have been killed in a possible drone strike in Dolbiyow Village, 35km east of Dhobley. The farmers and their camels were killed moments after al-Shabaab fighters fled the area in vehicles, witnesses said.
narrative: A suspected US drone fired two missiles, killing 4 farmers and 'at least 10 camels.'

bij_summary_short: 4-6 killed and 4 injured. Danda Darpakhel, North Waziristan.
narrative: On Thursday, the first of two drone strikes killed 4-6 people in North Waziristan.

bij_summary_short: 3-6 killed in strike on a compound. Zeba Pahar, South Waziristan.
narrative: Hours later, missiles hit a house and car in South Waziristan, killing 6 people.

bij_summary_short: In the first of several attacks on this day, a drone attack struck a house in the Azan district of Shabwah, but the occupants of the house had left two minutes earlier.
narrative: In the first of several attacks on the day, a US drone struck a house in Azan.

bij_summary_short: 5-6 alleged militants killed in strike on a vehicle. Danda Darpakhel, North Waziristan.
narrative: Three men stood near a car, talking. CIA missiles took their lives from above.

bij_summary_short: Drone strike killed 7-9 people, including a 16 and 17-year-old boy. Abdulrahman al-Awlaki, the 16-year old son of Anwar al-Awlaki, was one of the people who perished.
names: [Abdulrahman al-Awlaki, Ahmed Abdulrahman al-Awlaki, Sarhan al-Qusa]
narrative: While eating dinner with his teenage cousins, Abdulrahman, a 16-year-old US citizen, was killed by a US drone.

bij_summary_short: A third possible drone attack killed up to 17 people on Friday night.
narrative: A third possible drone attack killed up to 17 people on Friday night.

bij_summary_short: Saleh Qaid Toayman and his 14-year-old son were reported killed in an overnight strike in Azan. They were grazing camels 'in an area known to be controlled by al-Qaida,' and had then slept by a mosque, according to Toayman's 15-year-old son Azzedine who survived the strike.
narrative: Azzedine, 15, was grazing camels. His father and brother, 14, were 'scattered into pieces.'

bij_summary_short: 3-6 killed and 3-7 injured in strike on a compound. Angor Adda, South Waziristan.
narrative: US drones fired eight missiles at a building in Baghar, killing 4 people and wounding 3 others.

bij_summary_short: There were reports of a further strike in South Waziristan on Maulvi Nazir's forces, which killed up to seven alleged militants. Three of those killed were named as Hazrat Ali, Sher Ali and Amir Hamza - possibly 'low level Taliban commanders.'
narrative: 3 people killed. Nine missiles. From the rubble, three bodies: Hazrat, Sher, Amir.

bij_summary_short: At least 11 civilians died and more than 20 others were wounded after a possible US drone attacked on Afmadow town in the Lower Juba region.
narrative: 11 civilians killed and more than 20 wounded. Drones seen hovering for 'the last few days.'

bij_summary_short: 13-22 killed and 6 injured in a strike.
narrative: Two missiles struck the village of Bobar, killing between 13 and 22 people.

bij_summary_short: 4-6 killed and 3-4 injured in a strike on a vehicle. Azam Warsak, South Waziristan.
narrative: Maulvi lived. But his 20-year-old brother, Hazrat, and cousin, Meraj, did not. 4-6 killed.

bij_summary_short: A second strike of the day on either a moving vehicle or a house in North Waziristan killed 4-6 alleged militants, according to Pakistani security officials. No further details were given.
narrative: The second attack of the day killed 4 people in a house.

bij_summary_short: Strike on a vehicle killed 4-6.
narrative: 3 chromite miners--Khastar, Mamrud, and Noorzal--were killed in a car. 4-6 dead, 2 injured.

bij_summary_short: An attack on a vehicle near the town of Mir Ali, North Waziristan killed 2-4 people, including at two civilians.
narrative: Tariq, 16, and Waheed, 12, were driving to pick up their aunt. A drone ended their journey.

bij_summary_short: An attack on an alleged militant housing compound near Miranshah in North Waziristan killed up to three people and injured three others, according to local officials. Dawn reported that the casualties were part of the Haqqani Network.
narrative: 3 people killed in Darpakhel Sarai.

bij_summary_short: The militant stronghold of Rumeila was targeted by 'five US drone strikes,' killing an unknown number of people.
Yemen
lat: Five US drone strikes' killed an unknown number of people in Rumeila.

bij_summary_short: Missiles were fired at a training camp in Afgoye, Lower Shabelle, according to al Shabaab. 1-2 reported killed. Unclear who was responsible for the strikes.
narrative: 1-2 people were killed in the town of Afgoye.

bij_summary_short: 7 killed and 2-4 injured in strike on a house in Miranshah.
narrative: Nine people were sleeping. At 3:45am, a US drone fired missiles at their house, killing 7.

bij_summary_short: 16-22 killed in strike on two housing compounds in Babar Ghar.
narrative: Deep in the mountains, 15-22 people were killed by missiles from five US drones.

bij_summary_short: In the third strike in as many days, CIA drones attacked a compound in North Waziristan, killing 7-9.
narrative: In Razmak, at least 4 people were killed when US drones fired missiles into a building.

bij_summary_short: A US drone strike reportedly killed Abdulrahman al-Wuhayshi, the younger brother of Nasser al-Wuhayshi, a Yemeni who leads AQAP.
narrative: A US drone attacked the town of Zinjibar, killing one person.

bij_summary_short: 1-4 people killed in a strike on a house near Miranshah. Aslam Awan (aka Abdullah Khorasani), a senior operations operative for al Qaeda  is believed to be among dead.
narrative: Missiles destroyed a mudbrick house, killing 4. A mother and son, who were inside, survived.

bij_summary_short: 5-9 alleged militants killed and 2-3 injured in a strike on two vehicles near Dogga.
narrative: A US drone killed at least 8 people Thursday.

bij_summary_short: Three missiles fired from a suspected drone operated by JSOC killed British-Lebanese militant Bilal Al-Barjawi, also known as Abu Hafsa.
narrative: Hours after his wife gave birth in a London hospital, 27-year-old Bilal was killed by a drone.

bij_summary_short: 4-5 alleged militants killed and 1 injured in a strike on a vehicle near Deegan.
narrative: Up to 5 people were driving when the missiles struck. Their vehicle was 'engulfed by fire.'

bij_summary_short: 10-14 people killed in Abyan.
names: [Mouwhahhad al-Maaribi, Ibrahim Al-Najdi, Abed Al Farraj Al-Shamri, Saleh Al-Akili, Abdul Munim al-Fathani]
narrative: At least 13 people were killed from above.

bij_summary_short: 9-10 alleged militants killed and up to 12 injured a strike on a house near Miranshah.
narrative: Drone missiles hit a house, killing 10. 'Almost all the men were burnt beyond recognition.'

bij_summary_short: 5-8 killed, possibly 2 civilians, in a strike on a house near Miransha.  Badar Mansoor, a local Pakistani al Qaeda leader, and his wife and child are believed to be amongst dead.
narrative: Badar, living in a rented house, was killed with 4-7 others. His wife and daughter were injured.

bij_summary_short: 6 alleged militants killed and up to 7 injured in a strike on a house near Spalga.
narrative: A US drone killed at least 5 people in a house. Several others were wounded.

bij_summary_short: 10-15 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle in Mir Ali.
narrative: In the second attack of the day, drone missiles hit a pickup truck, killing 10-15 people.

bij_summary_short: Hours after Secretary Clinton told the London Somalia conference that airstrikes against al Shabaab 'would not be a good idea', a US drone strike killed up to seven alleged Islamists in Lower Shabelle.
narrative: 4 people dead. US official: 'a white Kenyan reported killed in the attack was not the target.'

bij_summary_short: 8-15 alleged militants killed and 3 injured in a strike on a vehicle in the Mandao borderlands area. Amongst dead was German citizen Samir H, believed to be one of the most dangerous Islamists in the country.
narrative: Samir was in a large pickup truck. Above him, a US drone. Missiles killed up to 12 people.

bij_summary_short: Two sources reported a second strike. The first reportedly hit a vehicle, killing up to 15 militants. The second strike was said to have hit a house 12 kilometres away, killing 'six Uzbeks.'
narrative: Seven miles from the first strike, a US drone killed 6 people in a house.

bij_summary_short: A late evening airstrike on Bayda by US drones struck a gathering of alleged militants. As many as 34 'AQAP militants' died. Two brothers of local businessman Salim al-Barakani - one a teacher, the other a cellphone repairman, were among the civilians killed.
narrative: Salim's two brothers -- a teacher and a cellphone repairman -- were killed with 21-32 others.

bij_summary_short: Air strikes in Jaar and Zinjibar killed up to 24 alleged militants. Although initially reported as the work of the Yemen Air Force, a senior Yemen government official told CNN that the attacks were the work of the US, part of a three-day offensive.
narrative: Up to 24 people were killed in Jaar and Zinjibar, bringing the weekend death toll to 58.

bij_summary_short: An air attack on a militant-occupied factory where arms were allegedly stored killed three near Jaar. Ansar al Sharia said US drones carried out the early evening strike, with up to five drones reportedly taking part.
narrative: Five drones struck the town of Jaar, killing 6 people.

bij_summary_short: 4-5 people were killed in a strike on a moving vehicle. CNN reported that the strike appeared to be the work of the US.
narrative: A US drone killed 4-5 people in a car.

bij_summary_short: 6-8 alleged militants belived to be senoir commanders of a Taliban faction were killed and 2-4 injured in a strike on a vehicle.
narrative: Hafeez, Shamsullah, Wajahat, and Abdullah were killed. 3 others were 'mutilated beyond recognition.'

bij_summary_short: 7 unknown alleged militants killed and 3 injured in a strike on a vehicle in the borderlands of North and South Waziristan.
narrative: Four drone missiles hit a house and pickup truck, killing 7 people.

bij_summary_short: According to local Yemen officials, three areas in Zinjibar were struck by US drone strikes, killing at least 30 al Qaeda fighters.
narrative: US drone missiles killed at least 30 people Thursday. Dozens of others were injured.

bij_summary_short: A Miranshah house destroyed killing 4 alleged militants.
narrative: One missile pierced the ceiling. More demolished five nearby shops. 4 people were killed.

bij_summary_short: Four alleged AQAP militants died and three were 'critically injured' after a US drone struck their vehicles. 6-9 others were injured, including 5 civilians. One of the civilians, Mohamed, would later die.
narrative: 4 people killed in a Hyundai. 6 civilians wounded; Mohamed died. A 'shower' of shrapnel.

bij_summary_short: Multiple airstrikes killed as many as 38 'suspected al Qaeda militants' in Lahj and Abyan over a 48-hour period, according to CNN. A number of officials confirmed US involvement
narrative: Up to 38 people were killed in 'multiple airstrikes.'

bij_summary_short: News agencies reported a night time US drone strike on a moving vehicle in Shabwah province. The Yemen Air Force lacks the technical ability to carry out such a strike.
narrative: On Saturday night, 8 people were driving to Marib. A US drone fired a missile, killing them all.

bij_summary_short: The Yemen Defence Ministry reported that 'Yemeni-U.S. joint air raids bombed al-Qaida hideouts in the southern province of Abyan, killing at least 16 militants', according to Xinhua. Other agencies did not specify US involvement.
narrative: US drones and Yemeni warplanes bombed the southern province of Abyan, killing at least 16 people.

bij_summary_short: The other militants, 8, were killed when a US drone targeted their car in the province,' alsahwa-yemen.net quoted a tribal source as saying.
narrative: In Shabwah, a US drone killed 8 people in a car.

bij_summary_short: A targeted evening strike on an 'al Qaeda convoy' reportedly killed up to 14 alleged militants near Loder, Abyan Province. A local government official told Xinhua that the attack was the work of a US drone.
narrative: On Wednesday evening, a US drone killed 14 people and wounded 10 others on a desert road.

bij_summary_short: An evening airstrike on a vehicle killed at least three Ansar al-Sharia members, among them reportedly Mohammed al-Sabri, a 'leading militant'. Associated Press cited two Yemen military officials as saying that US drones had carried out the attack in Al Bayda Province, with a security official telling AFP the same. Eyewitness Abdel-Salam al-Ansi told the agency that he heard a strong explosion and had rushed outside: 'The car had been turned into a ball of fire.'
narrative: 7 people were killed when a drone turned their car into 'a charred skeleton.'

bij_summary_short: Up to five drone strikes killed at least five militants in the southeastern Shabwah province. CNN reported militant hideouts, checkpoints, training facilities and weapons warehouses were targeted in the strikes.
narrative: Up to five US drone strikes killed 5-7 people in the town of Azzan.

bij_summary_short: As many as 17 alleged militants were killed in a series of of strikes in the south of the country. AFP said it was unclear whether the strike was carried out by the Yemen Air Force or US drones.
narrative: Missiles killed 12-17. 'Unclear' if strikes were carried out by Yemeni Air Force or US drones.

bij_summary_short: At least four militants were killed when a drone strike destroyed two of three cars driving through the desert area of Sanda in central Marib province. Two senior security officials told CNN that US drones conducted the strike.
narrative: US drones fired missiles at a car in Al-Samdah, setting it ablaze and killing 3-4 people.

bij_summary_short: A possible drone strike hit vehicles in Shabwah province leaving three dead and two injured. Local Mohammed Bindighar told AP he had seen drones circling overhead almost daily for the last five months.
narrative: 3 people were killed Monday. Mohammed, who lives nearby, said he sees drones 'almost daily.'

bij_summary_short: At least three alleged militants were killed in a possible drone strike in the southern city of Mudiyah. Reuters reported the strike targeted the alleged militants in a vehicle. Residents said they saw two drones after hearing an explosion.
narrative: After hearing an explosion, residents saw two pilotless drones. 3 people were killed in a car.

bij_summary_short: 3-6 alleged militants killed and up to 3 injured on a strike on an ex-girl's school in Miranshah.
narrative: US drone missiles struck a high school in North Waziristan, killing 6 people.

bij_summary_short: Three alleged militants were killed driving through the northern province of al-Jawf. A tribal source told AFP the car was completely destroyed and all its occupants killed. AP reported Yemeni officials 'had no details on the source of the attack or the identity of the three.'
narrative: 3 people were killed when a missile hit their SUV. 'No details' on their identities.

bij_summary_short: Four alleged militants were killed in an airstrike near the town of Loder. The strike hit a vehicle according to a local government official.
narrative: On Monday, while driving in a car, 4 people were killed near the town of Lawder.

bij_summary_short: A strike hit a vehicle near Zinjibar killing three alleged al Qaeda militants. A Yemeni presidential aide told CNN the Yemen government had approved a series of US drone strikes on militant positions in the south of the country. Since mid-April there had been at least two US drone strikes a day, the aide continued.
narrative: The third attack in two days hit a vehicle near Zinjibar, killing 3 people.

bij_summary_short: Three Yemeni security officials told CNN a US drone attacked a militant training camp outside the southern town of Jaar, killing up to 15.
narrative: Missiles from a US drone killed 13-15 people in Abyan.

bij_summary_short: 8-10 killed and one injured in a strike. Disputes on wether the dead were militants or civilians.
narrative: 9 people killed in Shawal. 'Pakistan said the drone strike was illegal and counterproductive.'

bij_summary_short: Fahd al-Quso, who admitted to being part responsible for the death of 17 US sailors, died in the attack in Shabwa province. Also initially reported killed was al-Quso's nephew Fahed Salem al-Akdam, described as a 'senior AQAP leader.' However the Washington Post later identified the man as 19-year old farm worker Nasser Salim, who was no relation to Quso.
narrative: Nasser, 19, was tending to his farm when Fahd arrived. The drone tore them both to pieces.

bij_summary_short: A series of strikes in the small hours killed up to 8 in Abyan province.
narrative: A US drone fired missiles at a house, killing 5-12 people.

bij_summary_short: AP reported two more alleged militants killed in a second strike on Shaqra, northeast of the provincial capital Zinjibar. The Yemen Observer reported AQAP claims that a drone killed four men in the strike.
narrative: A second US drone attacked the town of Shaqra, killing 2-4 people.

bij_summary_short: A reported US drone strike took place in al-Hosoon, near the city of Marib. A tribal chief told Reuters that 'a drone fired two rockets at two vehicles, killing five Al-Qaeda members.'
names: [Mohsen Abdul-Rahman Al-Youssefi, Saleh Mohammed Jaber Shabwahni, Abu Mutib Al-Yamani, Abu Laith Al-Hadrami, Abu Mohammed al Shihiri, Abu Abdullah al Sanaani]
narrative: In Shabwa, an apparent US drone strike set a vehicle on fire, killing its passengers.

bij_summary_short: Agencies reported a second strike of the day, also on a convoy of vehicles: 'One drone fired rockets at a convoy of three pick-up trucks travelling on a desert road in Hareeb area of Shabwa province.
names: [Ali Hassan Ali Gharib al Shabwahni, Hassan Saud Hassan Bin Mouaily, Hamid Nasir Al-Aqraa, Mohsen Saeed Kharassan, Ahmed Saleh Mohammed Al-Faqeer, Abdullah Ali Muhammad Miqan, Mohammed Saleh Bakeer Al-Faqeer, Aref Issa Chabwi, Mubarak, Saleh Al-Nasser Al-Nassi, Abu Obeida al Masri]
narrative: 7 people were killed on a desert road in Hareeb. Drone missiles destroyed three pickup trucks.

bij_summary_short: A possible third drone strike of the day killed between 6 and 10 alleged al Qaeda militants at a 'hideout', according to a local Yemeni official.
narrative: The last drone attack of the day killed 6-10 people near Aden.

bij_summary_short: At least 14 people were killed in an airstrike in a residential area of Jaar. Two or more strikes in quick succession reduced an entire block to rubble. Initial reports from government sources claimed two or three senior al Qaeda militants were killed as well as at least eight civilians. This changed as more details emerged in subsequent reports. Amnesty International identified 14 civilian victims by name - including a pregnant woman. Survivor Samir al Mushari told USA Today 26 civilians died.
names: [Mariam Abdo Said, Majed Ahmed Abdullah Awad, Nuweir al Arshani, Abdo Said, Salem Mohsen Haidar al Jalladi, Adeeb Ahmed Ghanem al Doba'i, Mohammed Abdullah Saleh Hussein, Munir bin al Haji bin al Assi, Ahmed Abdullah Ahmed al Shahari, Salem Abdullah Ahmed Abkar, Hussien Mubarak Ahmed, Abd al Rahman Motahhar, Hafez Abdullah Mubarak, Mohsen Ali Salem, Amir al Azzani]
narrative: 42 people--including 26 civilians--became rubble. 'The plane was gray. It looked like an eagle.'

bij_summary_short: Three alleged militants were killed in a possible US drone strike in the eastern province of Hadhramaut. Reuters reported a car apparently carrying explosives was destroyed when the overnight strike targeted a convoy.
narrative: 3 people were killed in a car. @BaFana3, a Sanaa-based lawyer, reported the attack on Twitter.

bij_summary_short: A second air strike of the day destroyed a vehicle in the southern province of Bayda. Sources told AFP and Associated Press the strike was carried out by a US drone.
narrative: A US drone strike killed 2 people in Bayda.

bij_summary_short: 4-5 alleged militants killed and several injured in a strike on a house in Datte Khel Kalai.
narrative: One year before the President gave a major speech, a US drone killed 4 people in a house.

bij_summary_short: 10-12 killed and 3 injured, mostly civilians, after a strike hit a house and a nearby mosque during morning prayers.
narrative: The second drone attack in 24 hours killed 10-12 people in a mosque.

bij_summary_short: 3-4 alleged militants killed and 2 injured on a strike on bakery in Miransha bazaar.
narrative: Drone missiles struck a bakery in the Miranshah market, killing 3-4 people.

bij_summary_short: Up to five alleged militants were killed and four wounded in a possible drone strike in the centre of the country. Anwar al Awlaki's brothers-in-law Qaed and Nabil al Dahab were targeted but survived.
narrative: A US drone strike killed up to 5 people and wounded 4 others.

bij_summary_short: In the second strike of the day five alleged militants were killed in the eastern province of Hadhramaut, including local commander Saleh Abdul Khaleq Ali Jaber. Local media later named others killed as Hussein Rabi, Malik Bakotain and Muhammad al Saqqaf. A fifth badly burnt body was not identified.
narrative: The second strike of the day hit a car. 5 killed. A 'badly burnt body was not identified.'

bij_summary_short: 5-10 alleged militants killed and 4 injured in a double strike on a house in the village of Khassokhel.
narrative: Two drone missiles hit a house in Mir Ali, killing up to 10 people.

bij_summary_short: 2-5 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle in Datta Khel.
narrative: Up to 5 killed. 'Vehicle caught fire and the bodies of the people inside were badly burnt.'

bij_summary_short: Local officials and residents told agencies that a US drone had killed 11 -12 men they suspected of being Islamic militants, who were meeting at a house (or 'communications compound') in al Mahfad.
narrative: A US drone killed 11-12 people in a house.

bij_summary_short: 2-4 killed - two alleged militants and possibly two civilians in a strike in a vehicle in Khawashi Khel.
narrative: Khalil and Rehmanullah were riding on a motorcycle when a US drone fired two missiles at them.

bij_summary_short: 7-10 killed and 7-10 injured in a strike on a house where a Taliban funeral took place. Possible civilian deaths.
narrative: A US drone fired four missiles at a group of people gathered in mourning, killing up to 10.

bij_summary_short: 1-18 alleged militants killed in a strike on a militant compound. Abu Yahya al-Libi, al Qaeda's effective number two, is believed to be amongst dead.
narrative: Up to 6 drones fired missiles at a house, killing Abu. More than a dozen others died as well.

bij_summary_short: US drones hit southeastern Yemen, killing as many as 27 alleged militants. 'Dozens' reportedly wounded.
narrative: US drone strikes killed 27 people. Officials: 'No senior al Qaeda leaders died in the attack.'

bij_summary_short: A US drone struck a house and car in Azzan, killing nine alleged militants in the early morning.
narrative: 9 more people were killed when a US drone fired missiles at a house.

bij_summary_short: 4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle traveling east from Miranshah.
narrative: 4 men were traveling in a vehicle when multiple missiles destroyed their car.

bij_summary_short: The Yemen Times reported a US drone strike hit Azzan in Shabwa province, described as AQAP's 'last stronghold' in the province.
narrative: A US drone strike hit the town of Azzan. 'Casualty figures were unknown'.

bij_summary_short: 3-4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a shop or house in Miranshah bazaar. AFP reports witness saying another instance of a follow-up strike.
narrative: Drone missiles hit a market, killing 3. 'When they started rescue work, another missile hit.'

bij_summary_short: A house in Shaqra was hit in a strike that killed six children and one woman. It was 'not clear whether the Yemeni air force launched the strike, or whether it came from a US military or CIA drone.' NPR told the Bureau the strike came after Friday prayers. Ali al Armoudi survived the strike and told NPR his four-year-old son and 6-year-old daughter 'died in his arms on the way to the hospital.'
narrative: A missile entered Ali's house. His 4-year-old son and 6-year-old daughter died in his arms.

bij_summary_short: An airstrike by an unknown party in northern Abyan killed Hussein Saleh, a worker with the International Committee of the Red Cross. According to an ICRC spokesman 'it was an air strike. We have no additional details whatsoever.' An ICRC spokeswoman told the Bureau by email that Saleh 'was out side an ICRC vehicle when shrapnel hit him. He died from the shrapnel injuries. The strike did not hit the ICRC vehicle directly.' Three other ICRC staff with Saleh were unhurt in the strike the spokeswoman added. Another ICRC member told the BBC that it was not clear whether the attack was the work of a US drone or the Yemen Air Force.
narrative: Hussein, a Red Cross worker, died in an air strike. Unclear if it was Yemeni plane or US drone.

bij_summary_short: A US drone has killed three alleged AQAP members, including one senior commander. The identities of those killed were not reported but a security official said a drone fired two missiles on a convoy which destroyed their pick-up truck. Military officials said the vehicles had been pursued by US drones, causing fear among local residents.
narrative: A US drone destroyed a small pickup truck in the suburbs of Aden, killing 3 people.

bij_summary_short: At least 4 alleged militants killed when a CIA drone struck a house in the late evening. The strike was reportedly targeting alleged militants linked to Hafiz Gul Bahadur.
narrative: On Tuesday night, a US drone killed 4 people in Shawal.

bij_summary_short: CIA drones struck a house killing 6-8 people. The strike came around 7am, reportedly destroying the house.
narrative: 8 people were killed when a US drone fired two missiles at a house.

bij_summary_short: Up to five alleged militants were killed in an evening drone attack. The Defence Ministry said two of the dead were senior AQAP figures named Hussein Rubay and Fahad al Harithy. It was not clear if one or two drones took part in the strike, and if one or two cars were hit. Witnesses said while four bodies were pulled from the wreckage of the first vehicle. But said 'the flames were so intense in the second vehicle that no one could approach to check for any casualties.'
narrative: Two drone strikes hit two cars; 4 killed. 'Flames so intense' no one could look for more bodies.

bij_summary_short: Airstrikes have targeted the only town in Abyan province 'where jihadists still have a strong presence.' US officials have confirmed American strike jets are flying missions over Yemen from nearby Djibouti.
narrative: Either Yemeni airplanes or US drones killed up to 13 people in Abyan.

bij_summary_short: In an evening strike, CIA drones struck a house killing at least 17. This was the first strike since Pakistan re-opened its borders to Nato convoys after a seven month diplomatic stand-off.
narrative: 17-24 killed. As rescuers retrieved bodies, drones continued to hover, firing more missiles.

bij_summary_short: 11-14 were killed when up to 8 missile hit a compound alleged to belong to militant comander Sadiq Noor, ally of Hafiz Gul Bahadur.
narrative: As many as 14 people were killed when US drones fired 8 missiles at a house.

bij_summary_short: 4-7 alleged militants died when CIA drones fired 6 missiles at a house. 1 or 2 vehicles exploded. The attack took place hours after Pakistan ambassador to Washington again called for a halt to drone strikes.
narrative: US drone missiles 'pounded a house and car', killing 5-7 people and injuring 4 others.

bij_summary_short: Up to five were killed and two more injured while traveling through east Yemen. A possible US drone targeted the men in an evening strike. 'A drone fired two missiles at an all-terrain vehicle - killing its five occupants,' according to a local official. The bodies 'were found completely burnt with the completely destroyed car'.
narrative: While driving through Hadhramaut, 5 people were killed. A drone fired missiles at their car.

bij_summary_short: Suspected US drones targeted two vehicles, killing seven in an evening strike.
narrative: 2 dead. Residents 'recognized the sound of the drone,' which had been flying overhead for hours.

bij_summary_short: Up to three people were killed and two injured in an evening air strike.
narrative: At least 3 people were killed when a US drone fired missiles at a small pickup truck.

bij_summary_short: At least 5 people killed as tribesmen gathered for Eid, declared early in Waziristan. One named militant was killed, and his wife. A house and car were hit in the attack.
narrative: As residents celebrated Eid al-Fitr, a US drone fired missiles at a house, killing 6 people.

bij_summary_short: Two vehicles were hit in an early morning strike, killing at least 4. The vehicles were reportedly traveling from Miranshah.
narrative: For the second time in 12 hours, a US drone attacked a village in Shawal, killing 4 people.

bij_summary_short: A further 2-3 people were killed when CIA drones returned, reportedly targeting the wreckage of the vehicles destroyed in the day's earlier strike (Ob286).
narrative: The third drone strike in 24 hours killed 2 people near the wreckage of Sunday's 1st attack.

bij_summary_short: Badruddin Haqqani, son of the Haqqani leader and the network's senior military commander, may have been killed when 5-25 people died in a 7pm strike.
narrative: Badruddin died in a signature strike. CIA drones fired six missiles, killing 5-25 people.

bij_summary_short: 13-18 people were killed and 14 injured in a coordinated series of strikes that hit villages in the Shawal valley around noon. The strikes came 'minutes apart'.
narrative: In a string of three drone strikes, US missiles slammed into a mud building, killing 6.

bij_summary_short: In a second strike of the day, CIA drones reportedly fired two missiles on a wall compound.
narrative: Minutes later, 4 people were killed in Dara.

bij_summary_short: In the third coordinated strike at least three people were killed.
narrative: In the 3rd attack of the afternoon, US drones fired 5 missiles at 2 cars, killing 3-8 people.

bij_summary_short: After twenty days without a reported strike, a suspected drone killed at least two people in vehicle driving from Hadramout to Mareb province. A second car reportedly escaped unscathed.
narrative: A drone fired three missiles at a car. Two missed. Residents pulled 4 bodies from the wreckage.

bij_summary_short: As many as seven people were reportedly killed as they travelled through the village of al Qatn. Up to four missiles were fired at the village causing extensive damage to homes and terrifying the local residents sufficiently for some to be rushed to hospital with shock. At least two civilians were killed in the strike and testimony from their relatives formed part of a submission to an April 2013 Senate subcommittee hearing on the constitutional and counterterrorism implications of targeted killings.
narrative: Salem denounced Al Qaeda. No matter. While arguing under palm trees, 5 men were incinerated.

bij_summary_short: Eight people were killed as they drove through Hadramout province, reportedly local commanders of the Yemen-based al Qaeda offshoot. One report said the men were traveling in an armoured car between Qatan and Khashgha when they were struck at 7.30am. Six bodies were taken to Seiyun hospital while two extremely burnt corpses were left at the scene.
narrative: 8 'heavily armed' men were killed while driving through the isolated desert district of Hawra.

bij_summary_short: Attacks at 9am on a housing compound and a vehicle reportedly killed 4-6 people.
narrative: US drones fired a barrage of missiles at a vehicle and a house, killing 4-6 people.

bij_summary_short: US drones or jets killed 12 civilians in a botched attack on an alleged senior militant. Eleven died immediately and one subsequently of his injuries. The fourth airstrike in six days, the casualties including women and three children according to local sheikh Ahmed Ali and other locals said a 10-year-old girl and her 40-year-old mother were killed. Both were corroborated by a report compiled by three human rights groups, submitted to a US Senate subcommittee hearing in April 2013. 'The bodies were charred like coal. I could not recognize the faces,' said Ahmed al Sabooli the dead girl's 22-year-old brother.
names: [Abdullah Muhammad Ali Al Qadari (25 years), Mabrook Mouqbal Al Qadari (13 years) (aka Mabruk  Muqbil al Daqari), Nasser Salah (60 years), Raselah Ali (55 years, Nasser Salah's wife), Daolah Nasser (10 or 12 years, Nasser Salah's daughter), Abdullah Ahmed Abed Rabbo Robich (28 years), Saddam Hussein Mohamed Massad (28 years), Ismail Mabkhout Mohamed (30 years), Abed al Ghani Mohammed Mabkhout (12 years), Masoud Ali Ahmed Mouqbal (45 years), Jamal Mohammed Abad (30 years),]
narrative: 14 people, 3 of them children, were packed into a Toyota. 'Chaos. Flames. Corpses.' 12 killed.

bij_summary_short: Up to six people were killed and three injured when a US drone reportedly fired eight missiles a house in Hadrhamout. As many as four of the dead were reportedly civilians, three foreigners and one Yemeni.
narrative: A US drone killed 5 people in the village of Al-Ain.

bij_summary_short: The Yemen Observer was the sole source to report that US drones killed four people including the brother of an al-Qaeda leader the US had attempted to kill days earlier. Abdulraoof Ahmad Nasser al Thahab was supposedly driving his car in the Qaifa area of Radaa when a drone attacked him.
narrative: On Saturday morning, a US drone killed 4 people in a car.

bij_summary_short: Seven people including AQAP's second-in-command Said al Shehri (aka al Shihri) were reportedly killed in a strike on a car and house in Hadrhamout, eastern Yemen, according to US and Yemeni officials. The following month, a recording purporting to be al Shehri emerged, in which he claimed the false rumours of his death were 'to cover up the killing of innocent Muslim civilians'.
narrative: A drone did not kill 'Guantánamo prisoner 372,' although 5-7 others died.

bij_summary_short: An airstrike killed at least two people in Abyan province.
narrative: 2-4 people were killed in Abyan.

bij_summary_short: A car was destroyed when to missiles and three to four militants, possibly linked to Hafiz Gul Bahdur, were killed. This was the first strike in 20 days, and the first after protests over a blasphemous video left up to 17 dead.
narrative: 3 people killed in a car. Official: 'The identity of the militants was immediately unclear.'

bij_summary_short: At least 5 were killed, inlcuding senior al Qaeda member Abu Kasha al Iraqi, when two missiles destroyed a compound at around 9pm.00
narrative: Around 9pm, a US drone fired missiles at a house in Mir Ali, killing 5-8 people.
target: Abu Kasha al Iraqi, Saleh al Turki

bij_summary_short: A US drone strike reportedy targeted either a car or motorbike near Mir Ali in North Waziristan, killing 2-4 alleged militants.
narrative: US drones fired four missiles at a car, killing 3 people.

bij_summary_short: A suspected drone strike targeted suspected al Qaeda or Ansar al Sharia militants in the mountainous desert region of al-Saeed in Shabwa province in the late morning, killing at least three and injuring several others. Local media reported five missiles being fired in a multiple strike.
narrative: Three US drone strikes killed 5 people. Residents: drones had been flying 'for nearly a week.'

bij_summary_short: A pre-dawn attack destroyed a compound belonging to Maulvi Abdullah, described as a local cleric, killing five alleged militants and injuring three more, according to reports.
narrative: Several US drones flew into the area before dawn and fired four missiles,' killing 5 people.

bij_summary_short: Four missiles were reportedly fired at a madrassa belonging to Maulvi Shakirullah, killing 16-26 and wounding many more.
narrative: A US drone 'fired four missiles at a madrasa, or seminary,' killing at least 16 people.

bij_summary_short: In a dawn attack, a series of missiles were fired at a targets on the outskirts of Jaar, apparently targeting al Qaeda militants on the verge of launching a suicide attack on military targets. Reuters reported three separate strikes targeted a farmhouse, although ANI/Xinhua claimed the strikes hit two separate gatherings of alleged al Qaeda militants and AP quoted locals saying they had seen two cars ablaze.
narrative: Drone missiles hit a farmhouse, killing Nader and up to 8 others, some of them local teenagers.

bij_summary_short: An evening strike on a car killed 'at least four' alleged al Qaeda members in Maarib province, several miles outside Maarib city, sources reported. Local al Qaeda commander Sanad Ouraidan al Aqili (aka Sanad Abdulla al Aqili) was reported to be among the dead. 'Aqili's three companions, whose bodies were blown to pieces, have not been identified yet,' a local policeman told AFP.
narrative: 4 people were killed when a US drone fired missiles at a car.

bij_summary_short: A grandmother was killed when a drone hit a house and car. Several of her grandchildren were injured.
narrative: Nabila's grandmother was outside her home picking vegetables when a missile came out of the sky.

bij_summary_short: At least three people were killed in a suspected drone strike in northern Yemen. Local al Qaeda commander Omar Saleh al-Tais (aka Attais) was initially reported killed.
narrative: 3 people were killed when a US drone fired missiles at a house.

bij_summary_short: As many as three people were killed in a suspected US drone strike. Their vehicle was destroyed less than 24 hours after President Obama was reelected for a second term.
narrative: Less than 24 hours after the 44th President's reelection, a US drone strike killed 2 people.

bij_summary_short: A few hours after Taliban commander Maulvi Nazir was injured in a suicide bombing, 1-4 people were killed in a drone strike.
narrative: At least 3 people were killed and 4 others injured when a US drone fired missiles at a car.

bij_summary_short: The second strike on the Shin Warsak area in three days reportedly killed Abdul Rehman al-Zaman Yemeni, described as 'a mid-level al Qaeda commander, equivalent to a colonel'.
narrative: US drone missiles killed a man 'who was praying in an open field outside his home.'

bij_summary_short: 4-11 were killed, reportedly including senior al Qaeda commander Sheikh Khalid Bin Abdul Rehman al Hussainan, in the first strike in North Waziristan for 43 days. The Prime Minster Pervez Ashraf complained to US ambassador Olson the same day.
narrative: Up to 11 people were killed when a US drone fired several missiles into a house near Mir Ali.

bij_summary_short: 3-4 were killed, including an alleged militant commander Mohammad Ahmed Almansoor. A compound and a car were destroyed in the strike.
narrative: On Sunday, a US drone fired missiles at a house, destroying two rooms, a car, and 4 people.

bij_summary_short: At least three alleged militants were reported killed in a strike on a house near Mir Ali.
narrative: Two drone missiles hit a house, killing 4 people.

bij_summary_short: At least two men were killed in a suspected US drone strike in the southern Bayda province. It was the first strike in Yemen for 47 days and local media reported it hit a car.
narrative: The first of two US drone strikes targeted a vehicle in central Bayda, killing 2 people.

bij_summary_short: Up to five more alleged militants were killed in the second suspected US drone strike of the day.
narrative: Drone missiles hit a soccer field, killing 4 people. Hamzah, 16, 'has not been the same.'

bij_summary_short: Missiles fired at a moving motorcycle killed two alleged al Qaeda militants near the town of Shehr, the site of a strike four days earlier.
narrative: 2 men were killed by a pilotless aircraft while riding on a motorcycle.

bij_summary_short: 4-5 people were killed in a strike in the Shawal Valley area on the border of North and South Waziristan.
narrative: US drones fired two missiles at a house, killing 4 people and injuring 2 others.

bij_summary_short: Missiles hit a Land Cruiser travelling on the outskirts of al-Manaseh village, near Radda, in the fourth strike in a week. At least three alleged al Qaeda members died, including Saleh Mohammed al Ameri, described by unnamed local officials as a senior al Qaeda operative. 'Their bodies were charred and the car was completely obliterated,' a tribesman told Reuters. 'Their bodies were not recognisable, but the government says they're from al Qaeda.'
narrative: 3 people were killed when a drone fired missiles at a vehicle.

bij_summary_short: In February AFP reported Adel al Abab (aka Adil al Abab, Abu al Zubair) was killed in the second of a pair of strikes in a mountainous region in the eastern Shabwah province. An al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula (AQAP) source told the agency: 'A drone strike had targetted Sheikh Adel al-Abab's vehicle but he escaped and fled to a mountainous region where a raid by another drone killed him immediately.'
narrative: Sometime in January, a US drone targeted Adel. It missed. 'Another drone killed him immediately.'

bij_summary_short: In one of their most significant strikes in recent years, CIA drones killed Maulvi Nazir, the powerful leader of the so-called 'good Taliban'.
narrative: Maulvi was killed on his way from Bermal to Wana. 'Five other people were also killed.'

bij_summary_short: A strike on a vehicle near Mir Ali, North Waziristan, reportedly killed 3-6 people.
narrative: A drone killed 3-6 in a car, firing '2 more missiles as people tried to rescue the occupants.'

bij_summary_short: At least three people were killed in a reported drone strike on a vehicle in a 'mountainous area' near Radaa. The following day Reuters reported that local tribesmen demonstrated in Radaa against US drone strikes. One told the news agency that 'seven innocent civilians' had been killed in recent strikes.
narrative: An unmanned aircraft fired missiles at 3 people. Their bodies were 'unrecognisable.'

bij_summary_short: Alleged TTP commander Wali Muhammad Mehsud - reportedly responsible for training suicide bombers - among the dead after as many as five CIA drones bombarded Babar Ghar.
narrative: Around 2:30am, up to 18 people were killed when US drones fired ten missiles in Babar.

bij_summary_short: Alleged al Qaeda deputy commander of militant training in Pakistan and Afghanistan killed in the first of twin strikes near Mir Ali
narrative: Yasin's wife and daughter died with him when US drones fired 8 missiles at a house.

bij_summary_short: At least 2 killed in second strike, 15 minutes after the first near Mir Ali.
narrative: Noor's two-room house was leveled by a drone. Residents: 3 of the 11 missiles did not explode.

bij_summary_short: At least three killed in a strike on a motorcycle and house or compound.
narrative: Six drones were in the sky. Missiles hit a house. More missiles hit a motorcycle. 6 killed.

bij_summary_short: The first of a barrage of strikes to hit central Yemen missed its target. Xinhua reported the strike missed a vehicle in an orchard in the al Masil area of Wadi Abeeda.
narrative: The first drone strike missed its target; missiles landed in a nearby orchard.

bij_summary_short: Several sources, Reuters among them, reported a drone destroyed the vehicle it missed in the first strike. However AFP reported the four occupants had escaped on foot after their narrow escape earlier in the evening. Associated Press, Al Jazeera and Yemen Post identified up to six possible civilian casualties over the course of the day.
narrative: Later in the evening, 4 people were killed when a drone fired missiles in Marib.

bij_summary_short: At least two were killed in the last strike of the night, although a military vehicle stolen from the Yemen army and carrying six was reportedly destroyed. AFP initially reported that the strike killed four people from the 'al Haytak clan, part of the Abida tribe' without specifying if they were also al Qaeda militants. However the agency subsequently reported five alleged al Qaeda militants perished in the strike, including Hamad Hassan Ghreib (aka Amhed Bin Hassan Ali Gahreib).
narrative: Up to 6 people were killed in Wadi Abida. It was the last strike of the night.

bij_summary_short: A fourth strike was reported by the Yemen Observer. Ali al Ghulaisi, spokesman for Marib's governor, said three alleged militants were killed when a car was destroyed in a desert area of Marib near the border with Jawf province.
narrative: 3 people killed in a car. 'Their identities are not yet known.'

bij_summary_short: At least two men were killed while driving on the Sanaa-Marib highway. Witnesses told Reuters a US drone targeted the vehicle northeast of the capital. Security officials said three people were injured in the strike.
narrative: Up to 4 men were driving on the Sanaa-Marib highway when a US drone fired missiles at them.

bij_summary_short: An evening strike reportedly targeted vehicles at an alleged militant training ground, killing at least three and injuring 'several'.
narrative: An evening strike targeted a vehicle in al-Jawf, killing 3-5 people.

bij_summary_short: A Toyota Hilux was reportedly 'totally destroyed' and the bodies burnt beyond recognition. Casualty reports have varied but a clear picture of the strike emerged in the months after the attack.
narrative: Up to 7 people died when a drone destroyed a Toyota. Bodies were burned 'beyond recognition.'

bij_summary_short: A second possible drone strike of the day killed two or four people according to conflicting media reports. The Los Angeles Times reported the strike hit two motorcycles - its intended target - and killing the alleged militants. However anonymous sources gave a contradictory account to Xinhua. They said the strike missed the bikes, hitting a house belonging to Abdu Mohammed al-Jarrah. Two of his children were reportedly killed and three more family members injured.
narrative: A second possible drone attack missed its target and left 2 children dead in their home.

bij_summary_short: CIA drones destroyed a house and killed at least 3. Between two and six missiles reportedly hit a building, which caught fire.
narrative: At noon, between two and six missiles landed on a house and killed up to 5 people.

bij_summary_short: CIA drones destroyed a house, killing at least 6, in an area reportedly dominated by the TTP.
narrative: 6-9 people were killed when a US drone 'pounded' two mud-built houses in South Waziristan.

bij_summary_short: Drones kill at least one alleged militant, reportedly on horseback in North Waziristan. The horse died with its rider.
narrative: A drone fired missiles at men riding on horseback, killing them and their horses instantly.

bij_summary_short: Either a house or vehicle was destroyed, killing at least three alleged militants.
narrative: Up to 4 people were killed at a market in Datta Khel.

bij_summary_short: At least four killed in first strike for 24 days. The dead were badly burnt and went unidentified after the third consecutive strike on Datta Khel set a house on fire.
narrative: Six drones had been hovering. At sunset, one fired missiles at a house, killing 4-6 people.

bij_summary_short: CIA drones destroyed a house in South Waziristan, killing at least four, the day after the ICRC's president criticised the US' drone campaign in Pakistan.
narrative: Drone missiles destroyed a house in Wana, killing 4-6 people and injuring 7 others.

bij_summary_short: Five alleged al Qaeda militants were killed in the first US drone strike in almost three months. Journalist and activist Farea al Muslimi, a native of Wessab, contested the depiction of al Radami as an al Qaeda commander, although he also reported the view that al Rademi could easily have been arrested. Al Muslimi posted updates to Twitter from Sanaa as information came to him from friends and family in Wessab. And he said most people he spoke to said al Radami was not a part of AQAP. Al Muslimi: "In an area like Wessab, there is nothing easier than capturing a man like al-Radmi. Two police officers would have been more than capable of arresting him."
names: [Hamid al Radami, Mukram Ali Ahmed Hamoud al Haj, Najem Addin Ali Abdullah al Raai, Ghazi Hamoud al Imad, Ismael al Magdishi]
narrative: In the farming town of Wessab, a drone hovered. 5 people were killed in a car.

bij_summary_short: A dawn strike on a house in Marib province reportedly killed two alleged al Qaeda militants and wounded up to three others. Local media reported a Saudi and an Egyptian were killed while a woman and child were injured.
narrative: Missiles hit a house at dawn, killing 2 people. A woman and child were among the injured.

bij_summary_short: US drones reportedly destroyed a truck filled with explosives, killed at least four people. The dead were allegedly militants although a 'local dignitary' told AFP he could not say whether the four 'were Islamist militants'.
narrative: On Friday night, a US drone fired missiles at a truck in Al-Mahfad, killing 4-7 people.

bij_summary_short: The second strike in three days killed two men in central Yemen. Two alleged al Qaeda members were killed 'as they left a farm on a motorbike' according to Yemen's defence ministry website.
narrative: The second drone strike in three days killed 2 men in a car.

bij_summary_short: The Pakistan Taliban's second in command Wali ur Rehman was reportedly killed in the first CIA strike in Pakistan for 42 days. At least three other people were killed in the attack in the Miranshah area of North Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone fired missiles at a mud-built house in Chashma, killing 7 people.

bij_summary_short: Two vehicles carrying alleged AQAP militants were destroyed in either two separate strikes or single strike by a pair of aircraft. At least seven people were killed in the attack. Anonymous and named Yemen officials have said US drones carried out the strike.
narrative: On Saturday, two US drone strikes killed 7 people in their cars.

bij_summary_short: A night-time strike reportedly killed seven alleged militants and wounded others on the border of North and South Waziristan, Pakistani intelligence officials said. 'The US drone fired two missiles targeting a militant compound and killing at least seven militants,' an unnamed senior intelligence official told AFP.
narrative: A US drone strike killed 7 people in Shawal.

bij_summary_short: Multiple missiles struck a vehicle in the northern province of al Jawf, killing between two and six alleged militants. A local reporter tweeted that Huraydan had died alongside two relatives, including his 10-year-old brother.
narrative: On Sunday, a US drone fired missiles at a car, killing Hassan, his brother, and 'three others.'

bij_summary_short: At least 16 people were killed when CIA drones hit a house and a vehicle in or around the Miranshah bazaar. Casualty figures were low in initial reports but rose as the day wore on. By around 11am local time Reuters and AFP were reporting 17 killed in the strike.
narrative: At least 17 people were killed when US drones fired four missiles at a house.

bij_summary_short: A drone strike killed two alleged militants riding on a motorcycle and damaged nearby buildings in the village of Mosaki, near Mir Ali.
narrative: On Saturday night, an American drone fired missiles at a motorcycle. 2 people were killed.

bij_summary_short: A night-time strike on two vehicles travelling in convoy reportedly killed at least four alleged militants in the al Mahfad district of Abyan province; some sources put the death toll as high as eight. It was the first reported attack in seven weeks.
narrative: A US drone killed 6 people in Abyan.

bij_summary_short: A drone fired missiles at a home in the Shawal Valley, killing at least five alleged militants, with some reports suggesting eight had died. News reports carried different, apparently contradictory narratives of the strike. Locals told NBC the drone struck as a group gathered for Iftar dinner - the breaking of the fast that takes place each night during Ramadan.'The militants, including Arab fighters, were having an Iftar dinner in the compound when the drone fired two missiles. Later, an hour after the drone had disappeared, a group of militants arrived and started pulling out bodies,'
narrative: 8 people were having dinner when a US drone fired missiles at them.

bij_summary_short: A suspected US drone strike killed three people in a vehicle in the southern province of Shabwa. Two Yemenis and one Saudi Arabian, all alleged militants, were killed.
narrative: Early on Tuesday, in the town of Saeed, a US drone blew 3 people and a car 'to pieces.'

bij_summary_short: A suspected US drone killed at least four people on the day Yemen's President Hadi visited the White House to discuss counter-terrorism and political reform. It was the third strike in a week.
narrative: In the fourth drone strike since Saturday, 3-4 people were killed in a car.

bij_summary_short: Four alleged AQAP militants were killed in a suspected drone strike. The men were killed when as many as five missiles hit their vehicle as they drove through the central province of Marib in the early hours. All four in the car were Yemeni and the attack 'turned [the vehicle] into a ball of fire', a tribal source told AFP.
narrative: Two US drone strikes killed 4 men in Marib.

bij_summary_short: At least six people were killed in the early hours in the second strike in two days and fifth inside two weeks. A drone fired at least six missiles at two cars in a remote area, witnesses and local officials told Reuters. Local residents said they saw two vehicles and several bodies on fire at the scene. One of the dead, Sarhan al Thamlaqi, was named by local paper Yemen Post. He was reportedly not on a list of 25 AQAP operatives wanted for planning operations in Sanaa and other Yemeni provinces.
narrative: Up to 7 people were killed when US drone missiles destroyed a pair of cars.

bij_summary_short: Up to six people were reported killed in the third air strike in three days and sixth in under two weeks - a frequency of strikes not seen since the start of the year. The strike destroyed one or two vehicles at dawn - according to Yemeni media one vehicle was destroyed, killing four, and the second escaped the attack. Reuters reported two drones took part in the attack, remaining over the strike area for 'a while after the attack'. A Yemeni official told the Associated Press the bodies were seen lying charred alongside their vehicle. The anonymous source said five of the dead were Yemeni while the sixth was of another Arab nationality. However local security officials told CNN only four of the dead had links to AQAP - two were civilians.
narrative: 6 people were killed at dawn. 'The drones circled the air for a while after the attack.'

bij_summary_short: At least two people were killed in the second strike of the day. The attack hit at around 4pm local time, destroying a car, reportedly a Toyota Hilux. It was travelling through the eastern province of Hadramout. Witnesses reported seeing drones hovering over the area since dawn.
narrative: The second drone strike of the day killed 2-3 people in a Toyota.

bij_summary_short: At least three people were killed in a night strike on Hadramout - the third strike in three days. An unnamed official told CNN one of the three dead was a member of al Qaeda. However Yemeni officials told BBC Arabic that four alleged militants were killed in Wadi al Jadd. And Reuters reported three men were killed as they travelled in a vehicle in an area called Ghail Bawazeer. Residents heard a large explosion and later saw the car destroyed, the agency reported. Anonymous US officials confirmed drones carried out the attack.
narrative: For the third time in one day, a US drone fired missiles at a car. 3 people were killed.

bij_summary_short: US drones returned for the ninth time in 13 days killing at least two alleged al Qaeda militants. The men were travelling in a vehicle through Lahj province when the drones struck. Some reports said the attack targeted two vehicles, which were transporting weapons. The drones either destroyed both or one vehicle managed to escape, depending on the report. The attack came late in the evening in a mountainous area of the province. Activist and journalist Farea al-Muslimi later tweeted that three civilian bystanders were injured, and provided their names: Sidki Muhammed Ali, Ali Abdullah Hassan, and Fahmi Ahmed Hassan.
narrative: At least 2 people were killed by a US drone while driving on a mountain road.

bij_summary_short: Reuters is currently the only western news outlet reporting a late-night drone strike in Shabwa province. A local official told the agency a suspected US drone attacked a vehicle. 'The car was completely obliterated and the two men inside it were killed,' he said. There was no information about the identity of the dead men, although Reuters described them as 'suspected Islamist militants'. Locals also mentioned rumours of the strike on Twitter.
narrative: A possible US drone strike 'obliterated' a car, killing 2 people inside. Unclear who they were.

bij_summary_short: A senior militant leader was targeted and killed in a pre-dawn strike. Suspected US drones attacked a vehicle between midnight and 2am, killing both occupants including senior leader Qaid Ahmad Nasser al Dhahab. Sources alleged US drones destroyed the vehicle killing two before returning to hit the target again, killing at least two more.
narrative: Hours after Qaid's marriage, two US drones launched missiles at his car, killing up to 6 people.

bij_summary_short: At least three alleged militants were killed in an attack on what was reported to be either a vehicle near a seminary or a house in the Mir Ali area. One person was reported critically injured and taken to Mir Ali hospital. The strike, which took place at around 12.30pm, 'destroyed the vehicle and severely damaged the walls of the seminary.'
narrative: At least 4 people died by drone. Official: 'We do not know the identity of those killed.'

bij_summary_short: At least five alleged militants were killed in the second drone strike in a week. Two or three missiles were fired on a house intelligence sources said belonged to the Haqqani Network in an area was reportedly under Haqqani control. Anonymous intelligence officials also said 'seven badly burnt and mutilated bodies were pulled from the wreckage after the drones disappeared'.
narrative: A US drone fired missiles at a house, killing 6 people. Official: 'death toll may rise.'

bij_summary_short: At least six people died in the first CIA drone strike for 16 days. Four missiles reportedly hit two houses. The identify of those killed was not immediately known, an anonymous Pakistani official said. Local TV news reportedly said the strike hit at 3pm local time. The houses were 'reduced to debris'.
narrative: Four missiles struck a pair of houses in Shawal. Up to 7 people were killed.

bij_summary_short: At least three were killed when drones fired missiles on a house in North Waziristan. The strike hit around 11am local time; the house was destroyed. This was the second drone strike on Darga Mandi this month.
narrative: On Sunday morning, a US drone strike killed 3-6 people in North Waziristan.

bij_summary_short: Drones hit North Waziristan for the second time in 24 hours, killing at least three. The drones again targeted a house, at about 4am local time according to one report.
narrative: The second strike in two days killed 4 people in Datta Khel. 'Several others' were injured.

bij_summary_short: Two people were killed in an attack on a vehicle. Four witnesses reportedly said the men were militants and were Somali. One was reportedly Ibrahim Ali Abdi (aka Anta Anta), a senior al Shabaab commander responsible for several bomb attacks in the country. Abu Mohamed, an al Shabaab militant, also said Abdi was among the dead.
narrative: Hassan heard a crash. Saw a drone 'disappearing far into the sky.' 2 people killed in a car.

bij_summary_short: US drones killed up to five and injured three more in the first strike for a month,. The unmanned aircraft targeted a house and car in or near a bazaar in Miranshah, the capital of North Waziristan.
narrative: A US drone fired missiles at a house, killing at least 3 people.

bij_summary_short: US drones reportedly killed TTP leader Hakimullah Mehsud in a strike on his car or house a few miles from Miranshah, the capital of North Waziristan. He was killed in what could be one of the bloodiest strikes of 2013: at least three and as many as 25 people were reportedly killed.
narrative: Four missiles came for Hakimullah, ending the lives of up to 25 people.

bij_summary_short: At least three people were killed when an airstrike hit a car or Toyota Hilux travelling in the Ghayl Bawazir area of Hadhramaut.
narrative: A US drone strike killed 3 men in a car.

bij_summary_short: At least five people were killed in the first strike outside Pakistan's tribal agencies. CIA drones reportedly killed a number of named alleged militants including a senior Haqqani Network commander. Several missiles were fired on a Madrassa reportedly linked to the Haqqani group in the Hangu district of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. The strike hit at around 5am local time.
narrative: Just before sunrise, a drone fired missiles at a seminary, killing 2 teachers and 3 students.

bij_summary_short: Up to three people died in a drone attack on a house near Miranshah. The strike hit around midnight and the house was reportedly destroyed.
narrative: Doctors at the Miranshah hospital received two wounded men. Missiles hit a house, killing 3.

bij_summary_short: At least three people were killed in a strike on a vehicle in eastern Yemen. A moving vehicle was destroyed and the bodies of the three alleged al Qaeda members were left charred, an unnamed Yemeni security official said. It was not possible to identify the dead, the official added.
narrative: A US drone strike killed 3 people in a car. 'The suspects' identification wasn't possible.'

bij_summary_short: The attack reportedly hit a wedding convoy or procession, killing civilians, although according to one source it targeted a dozen al Qaeda members. A security official said: 'An air strike missed its target and hit a wedding car convoy, ten people were killed immediately and another five who were injured died after being admitted to the hospital.' The attack 'left charred bodies and burnt out cars on the road'.
names: [Hussein Mohammed Saleh Al Ameri, Mohammed Ali Massad Al Ameri, Ali Abdullah Mohammed Al Tays, Zeidan Mohammed Al Ameri, Saif Abdullah Mabkhout Al Ameri, Hussein Mohammed Al Taysi, Motlaq Hamoud Mohammed Al Taysi, Saleh Abdullah Mabkhout, Aaref Mohammed Al Taysi, Saleh Massad Al Ameri, Massad Dayfallah Al Ameri, Hussein Mohammed Al Tomayl Al Taysi, Salem Mohammed Ali Al Taysi, Ali Mohammed Abdullah Al Taysi, Rajeh Ali Massad Al Taysi ]
narrative: Fifteen people were on their way to a wedding when a US drone 'missed its target,' killing 12.
Third drone strike of the week hit a car in Al Qatn, killing 2 people.
Floating on the river between Gerdi and Khyber, a boat was hit with drone missiles. 7 people died, 2 injured.

bij_summary_short: At least three people were killed in the first Christmas day drone strike on Pakistan recorded by the Bureau since the strikes began in 2004. Although the dead reportedly could not be identified, they were allegedly Afghan militants.
narrative: At least 4 people were killed when a US drone fired missiles at a building.

bij_summary_short: An attack on a vehicle killed suspected AQAP members in the southern city of Shiban. Initial reports disagreed on how many had been killed, with estimates ranging from one (Associated Press) to six (local news site Sahafah). Local officials told reporters the strike was carried out by a US drone.
narrative: A US drone strike killed 2 men in a pickup truck.

bij_summary_short: Several outlets reported that at least two people were injured when a suspected US drone strike hit a car on the main highway of Al Bayda province, near the city of Radaa.
narrative: On Monday, a drone missile 'missed,' injuring 2 people nearby.

bij_summary_short: Residents and local officials said a suspected US drone strike killed two alleged AQAP members in the southeastern province of Hadramout. Reuters reported that the drone 'fired at least one missile' on a car in Hadramout's Al-Qatan district, 'completely destroying the vehicle and killing two people'.
narrative: A US drone fired at least one missile, killing 2 people and 'completely destroying' their car.

bij_summary_short: Either a farmer or an alleged al Qaeda member was reportedly killed in an early morning strike. This was the first report of civilian casualties in Yemen in 2014. Witnesses told Reuters drones fired two missiles but shrapnel hit a farmer walking home in the early hours.
narrative: While walking home, a Yemeni farmer was killed by shrapnel from a US drone.

bij_summary_short: A reported drone strike destroyed a car. Local media named one of the dead as Mohammed Saeed Jardan - a local of Abeeda.
narrative: Driving along a road in Wadi Abeeda, 3-5 people were killed from above.

bij_summary_short: A suspected US drone strike on a vehicle killed an al Shabaab commander and others about 200 miles south of Mogadishu, Associated Press and a local media site reported. Anonymous US officials briefed the media on the strike.
narrative: On Sunday, a US drone fired missiles at a car, killing 2 people.

bij_summary_short: Quoting local sources, Andolu News Agency suggested Shebwani was sleeping by his car when the drone allegedly struck. 'The fighter Jaber al Shabwani of the Al Shabwan tribe was sleeping near his vehicle in an open area before the drone launched a missile that hit his vehicle and killed him immediately,' the sources said.
narrative: Jaber was sleeping near his car when the missile arrived. 3 people killed.

bij_summary_short: The second air strike in as many days killed at least one person, Walid al Jemayzeh. The attack reportedly narrowly missed killing Abdul Hameed Memon Hatem, a self-identified member of AQAP - reportedly a senior figure.
narrative: The second drone strike of the day killed 1 person in Abyan.

bij_summary_short: The third strike of the day killed two to four people. Local media reported two unnamed militants were killed along with two 'others', possibly meaning civilians.
