narrative: In the province of Shabwa, a US drone fired missiles at a car, killing 2 people.

bij_summary_short: The fourth strike in three days killed between two and four alleged AQAP members as they drove through northern Jawf province. The vehicle was destroyed in the attack. An alleged local militant leader, Ali Saleh Jraim (aka Ali Juraym), was reportedly killed with 1-3 unnamed associates.
narrative: 3 people were killed while driving through al Jawf. It was the fourth reported drone strike of the week.

bij_summary_short: At least one person was killed in the fifth airstrike on Yemen in eight days. Initial reports were conflicted - either one, two or four people were killed when one or two vehicles were destroyed. The attack hit at night, suggesting it was a US drone strike - the Yemen Air Force is incapable of flying strike missions at night. Three missiles were reportedly fired on the vehicle, destroying it.
narrative: On Monday night, a US drone fired 3 missiles at a car, killing 2 people.

bij_summary_short: An airstrike destroyed a vehicle, killing Moajab bin Aziz and Ali Hasan Hadhban.
narrative: 2 people--Moajab bin Aziz and Ali Hasan Hadhban--were killed in Jebel Jame.

bij_summary_short: Three were killed in the first strike in Yemen in 20 days.
narrative: Missiles struck 'two huts' in Mahfad, killing 3 people. 'Drones are still hovering over the area.'

bij_summary_short: A US drone strike on two cars killed at least 13 people -- three civilians among them -- in the Sawmaa area of Yemen's southeastern al Bayda province.
narrative: 15 people--including 3 of Salem's friends--were killed by a US drone.

bij_summary_short: A series of air strikes hit alleged AQAP training camps in Yemen's southern Abyan province. The attacks follow a reported US drone strike the previous day in which at least three civilians were reportedly killed.
narrative: After dawn prayers, three drone strikes shook Mahfad, killing 25 people.

bij_summary_short: Elite US and Yemeni Special Forces soldiers ambushed a car in Shabwa, an eastern Yemeni province to the north of location of the previous two attacks. At least three people were killed. Unnamed US officials told the New York Times the CIA had carried out the drone strikes.
narrative: Late on Sunday, another strike flipped a car in Shabwa, killing 5 people.

bij_summary_short: At least four people were killed in a US drone strike in Mareb. They were travelling in a vehicle travelling to a farm in the area. Witnesses named two of the victims as: Naif Faraj and Mousleh al Arahabi.
narrative: 6 people killed.

bij_summary_short: At least three alleged AQAP members were killed in a reported US drone strike on a vehicle in Wadi Abeeda - also the site of the previous reported strike.
narrative: On Wednesday night, a US drone strike killed 3 men in a Suzuki.

bij_summary_short: The first drone strike in almost six months reportedly hit a house and vehicle. Early reports put the death toll at three, rising to 'at least four' and as many as six people had died. An intelligence official said the drone targeted a pick-up truck parked against the outer wall of a housing compound, setting both on fire. But locals told NBC that the vehicle had been driving through the village when it came under attack, and the damage to buildings may have been unintended: 'Two nearby houses were partially damaged in the missile strikes, but the target was the truck,' said resident Yar Mohammad.
narrative: A US drone fired missiles at a truck, killing 6 people and damaging two nearby houses.

bij_summary_short: Hours after the five-month hiatus in drone strikes ended, drones fired multiple missiles at alleged militants, reportedly killing either six or 10 people.
narrative: Missiles split the night in Dande Darpa Khel, killing 10 people and injuring four.

bij_summary_short: At least five alleged AQAP members were killed when their vehicle or convoy of vehicles was hit by several missiles fired by a US drone.
narrative: Five people driving. A buzzing above. A missile arrived, ending the lives of 'all 5 passengers.'

bij_summary_short: The third strike of the month killed at least five alleged militants in the early hours - around 4-4.30am. Most sources reported as many as six missiles hit a house and a vehicle on the outskirts of Miranshah - the capital of North Waziristan. Some sources reported the vehicle was inside the walls of housing compound when the strike hit while others were less specific.
narrative: Ten years after the first CIA drone strike in Pakistan, missiles hit a house, killing 6 people.

On Saturday, in the southern province of Shabwa, a U.S. drone strike killed 4 people.
At dawn, in an area called Markha, a U.S. drone strike killed 2 people in a car.
Hussein saw it happen at sunset. Three men killed. Drone missiles left them 'completely burnt.'
Two missiles slammed into a house, killing 4 people.
Ibrahim spent five years at Guantanamo. On Sunday, he was killed by an American drone.
As they sat down for a meal on the waterfront of Mukalla, a U.S. drone strike killed 5 people.
In Ataq, near the al Farouq mosque, a US drone strike killed 1-4 people.
Four people were killed at the palace entrance when a drone missile hit their car.
Late on Saturday, a US drone fired missiles at a pair of houses, killing 5 people.

In the deep, forested ravines of Shawal, a US drone strike killed 5 people.
Several drones were flying. Four people were killed. Two missiles destroyed the car completely.
Nine people were killed in a house.
Near the port of Mukalla, a US drone fired 4 missiles at 3 people, 'killing them on the spot.'
On Wednesday night, a US drone strike killed 4 people in a car.
On Thursday, in the town of Rafadh, a US drone strike killed 5 people.
Abdul and Shuaib were driving with two others when a drone missile struck their car.
A U.S. drone strike killed 30 people.
Overnight, a US drone attacked a car in Abyan, killing 4 people.
A U.S. drone fired missiles at a house, killing 4 people.
At dawn, as they drove along the coast, 5 people were killed. 'Bombs hit the men in their car.'
Three people were driving through the desert region of Harib. A drone strike ended their lives.
Four people were killed in Mukalla.
Five people gathered for a meeting. They were inside a house. A drone strike ended their conversation.
Two missiles struck a house, killing 6 people. Four others were wounded.
A U.S. drone strike killed four people in a car.
On Saturday, two U.S. drone missiles hit a car in al-Jawf. 'The four men were not immediately identified.'
On the outskirts of Marib, a U.S. drone strike killed 2 people in a car.
Explosions shook Balad Amin. Five people were killed.
In Shanta Ameerika, or the Five Americas, a U.S. drone strike killed multiple people.

A U.S. drone fired missiles at a house, killing 5 people.
3 people were killed in a car.

Six more people died when a U.S. drone strike hit their car in Shabwa.
On Monday, a U.S. drone strike killed 3 people, 'badly damaging the office of public water.'
This morning, four missiles hit mud homes, killing 4 people and injuring three.
Paper is all that remained. Dollars, leaflets. And a car--charred. Four people were killed.
On Saturday, a U.S. drone strike killed 150 people.
Eight men gathered in a courtyard. Above them, a U.S. drone. Two missiles came out of the sky.
town: Al Hudhn and Naqeel al Hayala villages

narrative: In the early evening, about 20 miles from Jilib, Hassan and 2 others were killed in a car.
On Monday, and then again on Tuesday, they flew. "We think about 12 militants were killed."
Six people, including Abu Sameh, were killed when a US drone missile hit a moving car.
Five people were driving in a Toyota Hilux when a drone strike set their truck ablaze.
Two people wounded. Five people killed.
On Thursday, in the middle of the desert, two drone missiles destroyed a car. 2 people killed.
Maybe it was Mr. Mansour. Several US drones lit up a car near Ahmad Wal, killing 2 people.
On Friday, in south-central Somalia, the United States fired a missile at Mr. Da'ud.

location: Al Bayda, Marib, and Shabwah Province
narrative: Three U.S. drone strikes killed six people across Bayda, Marib, and Shabwah.
On Monday, a drone missile hit a home, ending the lives of 5 people.
While the U.S. announced its drone strike statistics, three people were killed in an SUV.
Fireworks. Or something like it. A missile from the sky. Three people were burned in their car.
A U.S. drone fired missiles at a car, wounding 4 people.
On Saturday, 3 people were killed in a car.
3 people killed.
Three drone strikes. In a military press release, the United States announced the end of 13 people.

Missiles struck a car in Rada'a, killing 5 people.

location: Al Bayda, Marib, and Shabwah Province
narrative: Nine new strikes. 28 people.
Jalal was driving through al-Baydah when a missile ended his life. 2 people killed.
A Sunday drone strike, the last of the Obama years, killed one person "in a remote area."
While the world was marching, Donald Trump's first drone strike killed 3 people in a car.
Carnage is the word. U.S. drones and commandos killed 30 people, including Dr. Awlaki's 8-year old granddaughter.
Two men were riding a motorcycle. A drone missile came out of the sky.

location: Abyan, Al Bayda, and Shabwah Province
narrative: More than 20 air strikes--both drone and 'manned'--were launched in Abyan, Al Bayda and Shabwah.
Abdul saw it all. "The drone chased them." As the taxi drove past a farm, four people were swallowed by fire.
Two brothers--Ahmed and Mohammed--were walking down the road. A missile whistled in. They never made 15.
